properties.headline: High Wind Warning issued January 31 at 2:01AM MST until February 2 at 8:00AM MST by NWS Cheyenne WY
properties.description:
...HIGH WIND WARNINGS ACROSS WIND PRONE THIS WEEKEND...

* WHAT...West winds 35 to 45 mph with gusts up to 70 mph
expected.

* WHERE...Central Laramie Range and Southwest Platte County,
North Snowy Range Foothills, South Laramie Range and South
Laramie Range Foothills Counties.

* WHEN...Until 8 AM MST Sunday.

* IMPACTS...Damaging winds will blow down trees and power lines.
Widespread power outages are expected. Travel will be difficult,
especially for high profile vehicles and those with campers.
properties.instruction:
High winds will cause travel difficulties for high-profile, low
weight vehicles and those with campers or trailers. Those
travelers should consider alternative travel plans. Use caution
if you must drive.

NWSheadline: HIGH WIND WARNING IN EFFECT UNTIL 8 AM MST SUNDAY
